  <Name>k__BackingField: Zechariah
  fancyName: 
  nickname: zec
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: A Call to Return to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
      content: "  In November[[COMMENT(0)]] of the second year of King Darius\u2019s
        reign, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave this message to the prophet Zechariah
        son of Berekiah and grandson of Iddo:  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>In the eighth month. </b>A number of dates in Zechariah
          can be cross-checked with dates in surviving Persian records and related
          accurately to our modern calendar. This month of the ancient Hebrew lunar
          calendar occurred within the months of October and November 520 <span class="ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da">b.c.</span>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, was very angry with your
        ancestors. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, say to the people, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies says: Return to me, and I will return to you, says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t be like your ancestors who would not listen or pay attention
        when the earlier prophets said to them, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies says: Turn from your evil ways, and stop all your
        evil practices.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhere are your ancestors now? They and the prophets are long
        dead. "
      comments: []
    - title: A Man among the Myrtle Trees
      content: "But everything I said through my servants the prophets happened to
        your ancestors, just as I said. As a result, they repented and said, \u2018We
        have received what we deserved from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies. He has done what he said he would do.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Three months later, on February 15,[[COMMENT(0)]] the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        sent another message to the prophet Zechariah son of Berekiah and grandson
        of Iddo.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>On the twenty-fourth day of the eleventh month, the month
          of Shebat, in the second year of Darius. </b>This event occurred on February
          15, 519 <span class="ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da">b.c.</span>; also see note
          on 1:1.
    - title: 
      content: 'In a vision during the night, I saw a man sitting on a red horse
        that was standing among some myrtle trees in a small valley. Behind him were
        riders on red, brown, and white horses. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I asked the angel who was talking with me, \u201CMy lord, what do
        these horses mean?\u201D\u201CI will show you,\u201D the angel replied.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The rider standing among the myrtle trees then explained, \u201CThey
        are the ones the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sent out to patrol the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the other riders reported to the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        who was standing among the myrtle trees, \u201CWe have been patrolling the
        earth, and the whole earth is at peace.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Upon hearing this, the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> prayed
        this prayer: \u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        for seventy years now you have been angry with Jerusalem and the towns of
        Judah. How long until you again show mercy to them?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke kind and comforting words
        to the angel who talked with me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the angel said to me, \u201CShout this message for all to hear:
        \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says: My love for Jerusalem and Mount Zion is passionate and strong. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But I am very angry with the other nations that are now enjoying
        peace and security. I was only a little angry with my people, but the nations
        inflicted harm on them far beyond my intentions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: I have returned to show mercy to Jerusalem. My Temple will be rebuilt,
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, and measurements
        will be taken for the reconstruction of Jerusalem.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:16 '
        content: 'Hebrew <b>and the measuring line will be stretched out over Jerusalem.</b>  '
    - title: Four Horns and Four Blacksmiths
      content: "\u201CSay this also: \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies says: The towns of Israel will again overflow with
        prosperity, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will again comfort Zion and
        choose Jerusalem as his own.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]]Then I looked up and saw four animal horns. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:18 '
        content: '  Verses 1:18-21 are numbered 2:1-4 in Hebrew text.  '
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat are these?\u201D I asked the angel who was talking with
        me.He replied, \u201CThese horns represent the nations that scattered Judah,
        Israel, and Jerusalem.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> showed me four blacksmiths. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Future Prosperity of Jerusalem
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]]When I looked again, I saw a man with a measuring
        line in his hand. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: '  Verses 2:1-13 are numbered 2:5-17 in Hebrew text.  '
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhere are you going?\u201D I asked.He replied, \u201CI am going
        to measure Jerusalem, to see how wide and how long it is.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the angel who was with me went to meet a second angel who was
        coming toward him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The other angel said, \u201CHurry, and say to that young man, \u2018Jerusalem
        will someday be so full of people and livestock that there won\u2019t be
        room enough for everyone! Many will live outside the city walls. "
      comments: []
    - title: The Exiles Are Called Home
      content: "Then I, myself, will be a protective wall of fire around Jerusalem,
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. And I will be the glory inside the
        city!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says, \u201CCome away! Flee from
        Babylon in the land of the north, for I have scattered you to the four winds. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Come away, people of Zion, you who are exiled in Babylon!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After a period of glory, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies sent me[[COMMENT(0)]] against the nations who plundered you. For he
        said, \u201CAnyone who harms you harms my most precious possession.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:8a '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
      - number: '2:8b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Anyone who touches you touches the pupil of his eye.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "I will raise my fist to crush them, and their own slaves will plunder
        them.\u201D Then you will know that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies has sent me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says, \u201CShout and rejoice, O
        beautiful Jerusalem,[[COMMENT(0)]] for I am coming to live among you. "
      comments:
      - number: '2:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>O daughter of Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Many nations will join themselves to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        on that day, and they, too, will be my people. I will live among you, and
        you will know that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        sent me to you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The land of Judah will be the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        special possession in the holy land, and he will once again choose Jerusalem
        to be his own city. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Cleansing for the High Priest
      content: "  Then the angel showed me Jeshua[[COMMENT(0)]] the high priest standing
        before the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. The Accuser, Satan,[[COMMENT(1)]]
        was there at the angel\u2019s right hand, making accusations against Jeshua. "
      comments:
      - number: '3:1a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Joshua, </b>a variant spelling of Jeshua; also in 3:3,
          4, 6, 8, 9.
      - number: '3:1b '
        content: Hebrew <b>The satan; </b>similarly in 3:2.
    - title: 
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Satan, \u201CI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        reject your accusations, Satan. Yes, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who
        has chosen Jerusalem, rebukes you. This man is like a burning stick that
        has been snatched from the fire.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jeshua\u2019s clothing was filthy as he stood there before the angel. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So the angel said to the others standing there, \u201CTake off his
        filthy clothes.\u201D And turning to Jeshua he said, \u201CSee, I have taken
        away your sins, and now I am giving you these fine new clothes.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I said, \u201CThey should also place a clean turban on his head.\u201D
        So they put a clean priestly turban on his head and dressed him in new clothes
        while the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> stood by.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke very solemnly
        to Jeshua and said, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says: If you follow my ways and carefully serve me, then you will
        be given authority over my Temple and its courtyards. I will let you walk
        among these others standing here.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen to me, O Jeshua the high priest, and all you other priests.
        You are symbols of things to come. Soon I am going to bring my servant, the
        Branch. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now look at the jewel I have set before Jeshua, a single stone with
        seven facets.[[COMMENT(0)]] I will engrave an inscription on it, says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, and I will remove the
        sins of this land in a single day.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>seven eyes.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: A Lampstand and Two Olive Trees
      content: '  Then the angel who had been talking with me returned and woke me,
        as though I had been asleep. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat do you see now?\u201D he asked.I answered, \u201CI see
        a solid gold lampstand with a bowl of oil on top of it. Around the bowl are
        seven lamps, each having seven spouts with wicks. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I see two olive trees, one on each side of the bowl.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I asked the angel, \u201CWhat are these, my lord? What do they
        mean?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDon\u2019t you know?\u201D the angel asked.\u201CNo, my lord,\u201D
        I replied.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he said to me, \u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says to Zerubbabel: It is not by force nor by strength, but by my Spirit,
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Nothing, not even a mighty mountain, will stand in Zerubbabel\u2019s
        way; it will become a level plain before him! And when Zerubbabel sets the
        final stone of the Temple in place, the people will shout: \u2018May God
        bless it! May God bless it!\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:7 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>\u2018Grace, grace to it.\u2019</b>"
    - title: 
      content: 'Then another message came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CZerubbabel is the one who laid the foundation of this Temple,
        and he will complete it. Then you will know that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies has sent me. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do not despise these small beginnings, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        rejoices to see the work begin, to see the plumb line in Zerubbabel\u2019s
        hand.\u201D(The seven lamps[[COMMENT(0)]] represent the eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        that search all around the world.)  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:10 '
        content: Or <b>The seven facets </b>(see 3:9); Hebrew reads <b>These seven.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Then I asked the angel, \u201CWhat are these two olive trees on each
        side of the lampstand, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and what are the two olive branches that pour out golden oil through
        two gold tubes?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDon\u2019t you know?\u201D he asked.\u201CNo, my lord,\u201D
        I replied.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Flying Scroll
      content: '  I looked up again and saw a scroll flying through the air.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat do you see?\u201D the angel asked.\u201CI see a flying
        scroll,\u201D I replied. \u201CIt appears to be about 30 feet long and 15
        feet wide.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>20 cubits </b>[9.2 meters] <b>long and 10 cubits </b>[4.6
          meters] <b>wide.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Then he said to me, \u201CThis scroll contains the curse that is
        going out over the entire land. One side of the scroll says that those who
        steal will be banished from the land; the other side says that those who
        swear falsely will be banished from the land. "
      comments: []
    - title: A Woman in a Basket
      content: "And this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says: I am sending this curse into the house of every thief and into
        the house of everyone who swears falsely using my name. And my curse will
        remain in that house and completely destroy it\u2014even its timbers and
        stones.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the angel who was talking with me came forward and said, \u201CLook
        up and see what\u2019s coming.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat is it?\u201D I asked.He replied, \u201CIt is a basket
        for measuring grain,[[COMMENT(0)]] and it\u2019s filled with the sins[[COMMENT(1)]]
        of everyone throughout the land.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:6a '
        content: Hebrew <b>an ephah </b>[20 quarts or 22 liters]; also in 5:7, 8,
          9, 10, 11.
      - number: '5:6b '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>the appearance.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the heavy lead cover was lifted off the basket, and there was
        a woman sitting inside it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The angel said, \u201CThe woman\u2019s name is Wickedness,\u201D
        and he pushed her back into the basket and closed the heavy lid again.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I looked up and saw two women flying toward us, gliding on the
        wind. They had wings like a stork, and they picked up the basket and flew
        into the sky.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhere are they taking the basket?\u201D I asked the angel.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Four Chariots
      content: '  Then I looked up again and saw four chariots coming from between
        two bronze mountains. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The first chariot was pulled by red horses, the second by black horses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the third by white horses, and the fourth by powerful dappled-gray
        horses. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd what are these, my lord?\u201D I asked the angel who was
        talking with me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The angel replied, \u201CThese are the four spirits[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of heaven who stand before the Lord of all the earth. They are going out
        to do his work. "
      comments:
      - number: '6:5 '
        content: Or <b>the four winds.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "The chariot with black horses is going north, the chariot with white
        horses is going west,[[COMMENT(0)]] and the chariot with dappled-gray horses
        is going south.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>is going after them.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "The powerful horses were eager to set out to patrol the earth. And
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CGo and patrol the earth!\u201D
        So they left at once on their patrol.  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Crowning of Jeshua
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> summoned me and said, \u201CLook,
        those who went north have vented the anger of my Spirit[[COMMENT(0)]] there
        in the land of the north.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>have given my Spirit rest.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I received another message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHeldai, Tobijah, and Jedaiah will bring gifts of silver and
        gold from the Jews exiled in Babylon. As soon as they arrive, meet them at
        the home of Josiah son of Zephaniah. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Accept their gifts, and make a crown from the silver and gold. Then
        put the crown on the head of Jeshua[[COMMENT(0)]] son of Jehozadak, the high
        priest. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Joshua, </b>a variant spelling of Jeshua.
    - title: 
      content: "Tell him, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says: Here is the man called the Branch. He will branch out from where
        he is and build the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, he will build the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        Then he will receive royal honor and will rule as king from his throne. He
        will also serve as priest from his throne,[[COMMENT(0)]] and there will be
        perfect harmony between his two roles.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:13 '
        content: Or <b>There will be a priest by his throne.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe crown will be a memorial in the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        to honor those who gave it\u2014Heldai,[[COMMENT(0)]] Tobijah, Jedaiah, and
        Josiah[[COMMENT(1)]] son of Zephaniah.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:14a '
        content: As in Syriac version (compare 6:10); Hebrew reads <b>Helem.</b>
      - number: '6:14b '
        content: As in Syriac version (compare 6:10); Hebrew reads <b>Hen.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: A Call to Justice and Mercy
      content: "  On December 7[[COMMENT(0)]] of the fourth year of King Darius\u2019s
        reign, another message came to Zechariah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments:
      - number: '7:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>On the fourth day of the ninth month, the month of Kislev,
          </b>of the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar. This event occurred on December
          7, 518 <span class="ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da">b.c.</span>; also see note
          on 1:1.
    - title: 
      content: "The people of Bethel had sent Sharezer and Regemmelech,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        along with their attendants, to seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        favor. "
      comments:
      - number: '7:2 '
        content: Or <b>Bethel-sharezer had sent Regemmelech.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "They were to ask this question of the prophets and the priests at
        the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies: \u201CShould
        we continue to mourn and fast each summer on the anniversary of the Temple\u2019s
        destruction,[[COMMENT(0)]] as we have done for so many years?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:3 '
        content: Hebrew <b>mourn and fast in the fifth month. </b>The Temple had
          been destroyed in the fifth month of the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar
          (August 586 <span class="ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da">b.c.</span>); see 2
          Kgs 25:8.
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies sent me this
        message in reply: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSay to all your people and your priests, \u2018During these
        seventy years of exile, when you fasted and mourned in the summer and in
        early autumn,[[COMMENT(0)]] was it really for me that you were fasting? "
      comments:
      - number: '7:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>fasted and mourned in the fifth and seventh months. </b>The
          fifth month of the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar usually occurs within
          the months of July and August. The seventh month usually occurs within
          the months of September and October; both the Day of Atonement and the
          Festival of Shelters were celebrated in the seventh month.
    - title: 
      content: "And even now in your holy festivals, aren\u2019t you eating and drinking
        just to please yourselves? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Isn\u2019t this the same message the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        proclaimed through the prophets in years past when Jerusalem and the towns
        of Judah were bustling with people, and the Negev and the foothills of Judah[[COMMENT(0)]]
        were well populated?\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Shephelah.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then this message came to Zechariah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says: Judge fairly, and show mercy and kindness to one another. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not oppress widows, orphans, foreigners, and the poor. And do
        not scheme against each other.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYour ancestors refused to listen to this message. They stubbornly
        turned away and put their fingers in their ears to keep from hearing. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They made their hearts as hard as stone, so they could not hear the
        instructions or the messages that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies had sent them by his Spirit through the earlier prophets. That is
        why the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies was so angry
        with them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSince they refused to listen when I called to them, I would
        not listen when they called to me, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of
        Heaven\u2019s Armies. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Promised Blessings for Jerusalem
      content: "  Then another message came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says: My love for Mount Zion is passionate and strong; I am consumed
        with passion for Jerusalem!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: I am returning
        to Mount Zion, and I will live in Jerusalem. Then Jerusalem will be called
        the Faithful City; the mountain of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies will be called the Holy Mountain.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says: Once again old men and women will walk Jerusalem\u2019s streets
        with their canes and will sit together in the city squares. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the streets of the city will be filled with boys and girls at
        play.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says: All this may seem impossible to you now, a small remnant of
        God\u2019s people. But is it impossible for me? says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says: You can be sure that I will rescue my people from the east and
        from the west. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will bring them home again to live safely in Jerusalem. They will
        be my people, and I will be faithful and just toward them as their God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says: Be strong and finish the task! Ever since the laying of the
        foundation of the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, you have heard what the prophets have been saying about completing
        the building. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Before the work on the Temple began, there were no jobs and no money
        to hire people or animals. No traveler was safe from the enemy, for there
        were enemies on all sides. I had turned everyone against each other.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut now I will not treat the remnant of my people as I treated
        them before, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I am planting seeds of peace and prosperity among you. The grapevines
        will be heavy with fruit. The earth will produce its crops, and the heavens
        will release the dew. Once more I will cause the remnant in Judah and Israel
        to inherit these blessings. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Among the other nations, Judah and Israel became symbols of a cursed
        nation. But no longer! Now I will rescue you and make you both a symbol and
        a source of blessing. So don\u2019t be afraid. Be strong, and get on with
        rebuilding the Temple!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says: I was determined to punish you when your ancestors angered me,
        and I did not change my mind, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But now I am determined to bless Jerusalem and the people of Judah.
        So don\u2019t be afraid. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But this is what you must do: Tell the truth to each other. Render
        verdicts in your courts that are just and that lead to peace. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t scheme against each other. Stop your love of telling lies
        that you swear are the truth. I hate all these things, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Here is another message that came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says: The traditional fasts and times of mourning you have kept in
        early summer, midsummer, autumn, and winter[[COMMENT(0)]] are now ended.
        They will become festivals of joy and celebration for the people of Judah.
        So love truth and peace.  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:19 '
        content: Hebrew <b>in the fourth, fifth, seventh, and tenth months. </b>The
          fourth month of the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar usually occurs within
          the months of June and July. The fifth month usually occurs within the
          months of July and August. The seventh month usually occurs within the
          months of September and October. The tenth month usually occurs within
          the months of December and January.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says: People from nations and cities around the world will travel
        to Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The people of one city will say to the people of another, \u2018Come
        with us to Jerusalem to ask the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to bless us.
        Let\u2019s worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.
        I\u2019m determined to go.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Many peoples and powerful nations will come to Jerusalem to seek
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies and to ask for his
        blessing.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Judgment against Israel\u2019s Enemies"
      content: '  This is the message[[COMMENT(0)]] from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        against the land of Aram[[COMMENT(1)]] and the city of Damascus, for the
        eyes of humanity, including all the tribes of Israel, are on the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:1a '
        content: 'Hebrew <b>An Oracle: The message.</b>'
      - number: '9:1b '
        content: Hebrew <b>land of Hadrach.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Doom is certain for Hamath,near Damascus,and for the cities of Tyre
        and Sidon,though they are so clever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Tyre has built a strong fortressand has made silver and goldas plentiful
        as dust in the streets!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But now the Lord will strip away Tyre\u2019s possessionsand hurl
        its fortifications into the sea,and it will be burned to the ground.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The city of Ashkelon will see Tyre falland will be filled with fear.Gaza
        will shake with terror,as will Ekron, for their hopes will be dashed.Gaza\u2019s
        king will be killed,and Ashkelon will be deserted.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Foreigners will occupy the city of Ashdod.I will destroy the pride
        of the Philistines.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will grab the bloody meat from their mouthsand snatch the detestable
        sacrifices from their teeth.Then the surviving Philistines will worship our
        Godand become like a clan in Judah.[[COMMENT(0)]]The Philistines of Ekron
        will join my people,as the ancient Jebusites once did.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>like a leader in Judah.</b>
    - title: "Zion\u2019s Coming King"
      content: "I will guard my Templeand protect it from invading armies.I am watching
        closely to ensurethat no more foreign oppressors overrun my people\u2019s
        land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Rejoice, O people of Zion![[COMMENT(0)]]Shout in triumph, O people
        of Jerusalem!Look, your king is coming to you.He is righteous and victorious,[[COMMENT(1)]]yet
        he is humble, riding on a donkey\u2014riding on a donkey\u2019s colt.  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:9a '
        content: Hebrew <b>O daughter of Zion!</b>
      - number: '9:9b '
        content: Hebrew <b>and is being vindicated.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I will remove the battle chariots from Israel[[COMMENT(0)]]and the
        warhorses from Jerusalem.I will destroy all the weapons used in battle,and
        your king will bring peace to the nations.His realm will stretch from sea
        to seaand from the Euphrates River[[COMMENT(1)]] to the ends of the earth.[[COMMENT(2)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:10a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ephraim, </b>referring to the northern kingdom of Israel;
          also in 9:13.
      - number: '9:10b '
        content: Hebrew <b>the river.</b>
      - number: '9:10c '
        content: Or <b>the end of the land.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Because of the covenant I made with you,sealed with blood,I will
        free your prisonersfrom death in a waterless dungeon.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Come back to the place of safety,all you prisoners who still have
        hope!I promise this very daythat I will repay two blessings for each of your
        troubles.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Judah is my bow,and Israel is my arrow.Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]] is
        my sword,and like a warrior, I will brandish it against the Greeks.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:13a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
      - number: '9:13b '
        content: Hebrew <b>the sons of Javan.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will appear above his people;his
        arrows will fly like lightning!The Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will sound the ram\u2019s hornand attack like a whirlwind from the southern
        desert.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies will protect
        his people,and they will defeat their enemies by hurling great stones.They
        will shout in battle as though drunk with wine.They will be filled with blood
        like a bowl,drenched with blood like the corners of the altar.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God will rescue
        his people,just as a shepherd rescues his sheep.They will sparkle in his
        landlike jewels in a crown.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> Will Restore His People
      content: '  Ask the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for rain in the spring,for
        he makes the storm clouds.And he will send showers of rainso every field
        becomes a lush pasture.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Household gods give worthless advice,fortune-tellers predict only
        lies,and interpreters of dreams pronouncefalsehoods that give no comfort.So
        my people are wandering like lost sheep;they are attacked because they have
        no shepherd.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy anger burns against your shepherds,and I will punish these
        leaders.[[COMMENT(0)]]For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies has arrivedto look after Judah, his flock.He will make them strong
        and glorious,like a proud warhorse in battle.  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:3 '
        content: Or <b>these male goats.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'From Judah will come the cornerstone,the tent peg,the bow for battle,and
        all the rulers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will be like mighty warriors in battle,trampling their enemies
        in the mud under their feet.Since the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is with
        them as they fight,they will overthrow even the enemy\u2019s horsemen.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will strengthen Judah and save Israel[[COMMENT(0)]];I will
        restore them because of my compassion.It will be as though I had never rejected
        them,for I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God, who will hear their
        cries.  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>save the house of Joseph.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The people of Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] will become like mighty warriors,and
        their hearts will be made happy as if by wine.Their children, too, will see
        it and be glad;their hearts will rejoice in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Ephraim.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'When I whistle to them, they will come running,for I have redeemed
        them.From the few who are left,they will grow as numerous as they were before.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Though I have scattered them like seeds among the nations,they will
        still remember me in distant lands.They and their children will surviveand
        return again to Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will bring them back from Egyptand gather them from Assyria.I will
        resettle them in Gilead and Lebanonuntil there is no more room for them all.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will pass safely through the sea of distress,[[COMMENT(0)]]for
        the waves of the sea will be held back,and the waters of the Nile will dry
        up.The pride of Assyria will be crushed,and the rule of Egypt will end.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:11 '
        content: Or <b>the sea of Egypt, </b>referring to the Red Sea.
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Open your doors, Lebanon,so that fire may devour your cedar forests.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Weep, you cypress trees, for all the ruined cedars;the most majestic
        ones have fallen.Weep, you oaks of Bashan,for the thick forests have been
        cut down.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Good and Evil Shepherds
      content: 'Listen to the wailing of the shepherds,for their rich pastures are
        destroyed.Hear the young lions roaring,for their thickets in the Jordan Valley
        are ruined.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God says: \u201CGo
        and care for the flock that is intended for slaughter. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The buyers slaughter their sheep without remorse. The sellers say,
        \u2018Praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>! Now I\u2019m rich!\u2019 Even
        the shepherds have no compassion for them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Likewise, I will no longer have pity on the people of the land,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. \u201CI will let them fall into each
        other\u2019s hands and into the hands of their king. They will turn the land
        into a wilderness, and I will not rescue them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I cared for the flock intended for slaughter\u2014the flock that
        was oppressed. Then I took two shepherd\u2019s staffs and named one Favor
        and the other Union. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I got rid of their three evil shepherds in a single month.But I became
        impatient with these sheep, and they hated me, too. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I told them, \u201CI won\u2019t be your shepherd any longer. If
        you die, you die. If you are killed, you are killed. And let those who remain
        devour each other!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I took my staff called Favor and cut it in two, showing that
        I had revoked the covenant I had made with all the nations. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That was the end of my covenant with them. The suffering flock was
        watching me, and they knew that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was speaking
        through my actions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I said to them, \u201CIf you like, give me my wages, whatever
        I am worth; but only if you want to.\u201D So they counted out for my wages
        thirty pieces of silver.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CThrow it to
        the potter[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D\u2014this magnificent sum at which they valued
        me! So I took the thirty coins and threw them to the potter in the Temple
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:13 '
        content: Syriac version reads <b>into the treasury; </b>also in 11:13b. Compare
          Matt 27:6-10.
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I took my other staff, Union, and cut it in two, showing that
        the bond of unity between Judah and Israel was broken.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CGo again and
        play the part of a worthless shepherd. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This illustrates how I will give this nation a shepherd who will
        not care for those who are dying, nor look after the young, nor heal the
        injured, nor feed the healthy. Instead, this shepherd will eat the meat of
        the fattest sheep and tear off their hooves.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Future Deliverance for Jerusalem
      content: "  This[[COMMENT(0)]] message concerning the fate of Israel came from
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: \u201CThis message is from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        who stretched out the heavens, laid the foundations of the earth, and formed
        the human spirit. "
      comments:
      - number: '12:1 '
        content: 'Hebrew <b>An Oracle: This.</b>'
    - title: 
      content: 'I will make Jerusalem like an intoxicating drink that makes the nearby
        nations stagger when they send their armies to besiege Jerusalem and Judah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On that day I will make Jerusalem an immovable rock. All the nations
        will gather against it to try to move it, but they will only hurt themselves.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COn that day,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CI
        will cause every horse to panic and every rider to lose his nerve. I will
        watch over the people of Judah, but I will blind all the horses of their
        enemies. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the clans of Judah will say to themselves, \u2018The people of
        Jerusalem have found strength in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, their God.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COn that day I will make the clans of Judah like a flame that
        sets a woodpile ablaze or like a burning torch among sheaves of grain. They
        will burn up all the neighboring nations right and left, while the people
        living in Jerusalem remain secure.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will give victory to the rest
        of Judah first, before Jerusalem, so that the people of Jerusalem and the
        royal line of David will not have greater honor than the rest of Judah. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will defend the people
        of Jerusalem; the weakest among them will be as mighty as King David! And
        the royal descendants will be like God, like the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        who goes before them! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For on that day I will begin to destroy all the nations that come
        against Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen I will pour out a spirit[[COMMENT(0)]] of grace and prayer
        on the family of David and on the people of Jerusalem. They will look on
        me whom they have pierced and mourn for him as for an only son. They will
        grieve bitterly for him as for a firstborn son who has died. "
      comments:
      - number: '12:10 '
        content: Or <b>the Spirit.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The sorrow and mourning in Jerusalem on that day will be like the
        great mourning for Hadad-rimmon in the valley of Megiddo.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAll Israel will mourn, each clan by itself, and with the husbands
        separate from their wives. The clan of David will mourn alone, as will the
        clan of Nathan, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the clan of Levi, and the clan of Shimei. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Fountain of Cleansing
      content: "  \u201COn that day a fountain will be opened for the dynasty of
        David and for the people of Jerusalem, a fountain to cleanse them from all
        their sins and impurity.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd on that day,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies, \u201CI will erase idol worship throughout the land,
        so that even the names of the idols will be forgotten. I will remove from
        the land both the false prophets and the spirit of impurity that came with
        them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If anyone continues to prophesy, his own father and mother will tell
        him, \u2018You must die, for you have prophesied lies in the name of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019 And as he prophesies, his own father and
        mother will stab him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COn that day people will be ashamed to claim the prophetic gift.
        No one will pretend to be a prophet by wearing prophet\u2019s clothes. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will say, \u2018I\u2019m no prophet; I\u2019m a farmer. I began
        working for a farmer as a boy.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: The Scattering of the Sheep
      content: "And if someone asks, \u2018Then what about those wounds on your chest?[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2019
        he will say, \u2018I was wounded at my friends\u2019 house!\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>wounds between your hands?</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAwake, O sword, against my shepherd,the man who is my partner,\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.\u201CStrike down
        the shepherd,and the sheep will be scattered,and I will turn against the
        lambs.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Two-thirds of the people in the landwill be cut off and die,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CBut one-third will be left in
        the land.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> Will Rule the Earth
      content: '  Watch, for the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is coming
        when your possessions will be plundered right in front of you! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will gather all the nations to fight against Jerusalem. The city
        will be taken, the houses looted, and the women raped. Half the population
        will be taken into captivity, and the rest will be left among the ruins of
        the city.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will go out to fight against
        those nations, as he has fought in times past. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On that day his feet will stand on the Mount of Olives, east of Jerusalem.
        And the Mount of Olives will split apart, making a wide valley running from
        east to west. Half the mountain will move toward the north and half toward
        the south. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will flee through this valley, for it will reach across to Azal.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Yes, you will flee as you did from the earthquake in the days of King Uzziah
        of Judah. Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God will come, and all
        his holy ones with him.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:5a '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
      - number: '14:5b '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>with you.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'On that day the sources of light will no longer shine,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the precious ones shall diminish; </b>or <b>the precious
          ones and frost. </b>The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: 'yet there will be continuous day! Only the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        knows how this could happen. There will be no normal day and night, for at
        evening time it will still be light.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On that day life-giving waters will flow out from Jerusalem, half
        toward the Dead Sea and half toward the Mediterranean,[[COMMENT(0)]] flowing
        continuously in both summer and winter.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>half toward the eastern sea and half toward the western
          sea.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be king over all the earth.
        On that day there will be one <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2014his name alone
        will be worshiped.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All the land from Geba, north of Judah, to Rimmon, south of Jerusalem,
        will become one vast plain. But Jerusalem will be raised up in its original
        place and will be inhabited all the way from the Benjamin Gate over to the
        site of the old gate, then to the Corner Gate, and from the Tower of Hananel
        to the king\u2019s winepresses. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And Jerusalem will be filled, safe at last, never again to be cursed
        and destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will send a plague on all the
        nations that fought against Jerusalem. Their people will become like walking
        corpses, their flesh rotting away. Their eyes will rot in their sockets,
        and their tongues will rot in their mouths. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On that day they will be terrified, stricken by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        with great panic. They will fight their neighbors hand to hand. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Judah, too, will be fighting at Jerusalem. The wealth of all the
        neighboring nations will be captured\u2014great quantities of gold and silver
        and fine clothing. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This same plague will strike the horses, mules, camels, donkeys,
        and all the other animals in the enemy camps.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In the end, the enemies of Jerusalem who survive the plague will
        go up to Jerusalem each year to worship the King, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies, and to celebrate the Festival of Shelters. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Any nation in the world that refuses to come to Jerusalem to worship
        the King, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, will have
        no rain. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If the people of Egypt refuse to attend the festival, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will punish[[COMMENT(0)]] them with the same plague that he sends on the
        other nations who refuse to go. '
      comments:
      - number: '14:18 '
        content: As in some Hebrew manuscripts and Greek and Syriac versions; Masoretic
          Text reads <b>will not punish.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Egypt and the other nations will all be punished if they don\u2019t
        go to celebrate the Festival of Shelters.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On that day even the harness bells of the horses will be inscribed
        with these words: <smallcaps>Holy to the Lord</smallcaps>. And the cooking
        pots in the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be as sacred as
        the basins used beside the altar. '
      comments: []
